Okechukwu Nnodim, Abuja The Federal Government has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Ernst & Young in accordance with plans to concession the Calabar and Kano Special Economic Zones. It was gathered at the Federal Ministry of Industry, Trade and Investment on Thursday that Ernst and Young had earlier emerged the preferred transaction partner for the SEZs. On June 12, 2018, the National Council on Privatisation approved the reform of the two Special Economic Zones. The FMITI said a total of nine firms were shortlisted from the national database to compete for the provision of transaction advisory services for the reform of the two SEZs. On Thursday in Abuja, the MoU between the Federal Government and the multinational professional services company, was signed in Abuja by the Minister of Industry, Trade and Investment, Niyi Adebayo, and the Director-General, Bureau of Public Enterprises Mr. Alex Okoh, on behalf of the government. Mr. Damilola Aloba signed for Ernst & Young. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact:Â theeditor@punchng.com  